<paragraph blockId="8.[178,1086,506,587]" pageId="8" pageNumber="913">
E t y m o l o g y: The specific epithet is the combination of the two Latin adjectives: 
<emphasis box="[178,238,536,557]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="913">laetus</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[260,273,536,557]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="913">a</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[294,325,536,557]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="913">um</emphasis>
(pleasant) and 
<emphasis box="[481,541,536,557]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="913">pictus</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[562,575,536,557]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="913">a</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[596,627,536,557]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="913">um</emphasis>
(painted). It refers to the bright coloration of the species.
</paragraph>
